{\footnote # IDH_PYTHON_06}
{\footnote $ Python - Instructions de controle}
{\footnote K Python controle;if elif else;while else;for else;break continue pass;match case;PEP 634;try except finally;ExceptionGroup;with context manager;raise;return yield}
\b\fs24 Instructions de controle \b0\fs20\par
\par
6.1 if/elif/else\par
\par
{\f1   if x > 0:}\par
{\f1       print("positif")}\par
{\f1   elif x == 0:}\par
{\f1       print("zero")}\par
{\f1   else:}\par
{\f1       print("negatif")}\par
\par
6.2 while\par
\par
{\f1   while cond:}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
{\f1   else:                          # execute si pas de break}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
\par
6.3 for\par
\par
{\f1   for x in iterable:}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
{\f1   else:}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
\par
{\f1   for i, v in enumerate(liste):}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
\par
{\f1   for cle, val in dico.items():}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
\par
6.4 break, continue, pass\par
\par
{\f1   for x in xs:}\par
{\f1       if x < 0: continue}\par
{\f1       if x > 100: break}\par
{\f1       if x == 0: pass}\par
\par
6.5 match/case (Python 3.10+)\par
\par
{\f1   match commande.split():}\par
{\f1       case ["quit"]:}\par
{\f1           ...}\par
{\f1       case ["go", direction]:}\par
{\f1           aller(direction)}\par
{\f1       case ["look"] | ["regarder"]:}\par
{\f1           ...}\par
{\f1       case [action, *params] if action in \{"prendre", "deposer"\}:}\par
{\f1           ...}\par
{\f1       case _:}\par
{\f1           erreur()}\par
\par
Patterns supportes : litterales, capture, sequence, mapping, classe,\par
disjonction (|), garde (if), wildcard (_).\par
\par
6.6 try / except / else / finally\par
\par
{\f1   try:}\par
{\f1       x = int(s)}\par
{\f1   except ValueError as e:}\par
{\f1       print(f"erreur: \{e\}")}\par
{\f1   except (TypeError, KeyError):}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
{\f1   else:                          # execute si pas d'exception}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
{\f1   finally:                       # toujours execute}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
\par
Exception groups (Python 3.11+) :\par
{\f1   try:}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
{\f1   except* TypeError as eg:}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
{\f1   except* ValueError as eg:}\par
{\f1       ...}\par
\par
6.7 with (context manager)\par
\par
{\f1   with open("a.txt") as f:}\par
{\f1       data = f.read()}\par
\par
{\f1   with open("a.txt") as f, open("b.txt", "w") as g:}\par
{\f1       g.write(f.read())}\par
\par
6.8 raise\par
\par
{\f1   raise ValueError("message")}\par
{\f1   raise IndexError("...") from autre_exception}\par
\par
6.9 return, yield, yield from\par
\par
{\f1   def f():}\par
{\f1       return 42}\par
\par
{\f1   def gen():}\par
{\f1       yield 1}\par
{\f1       yield 2}\par
{\f1       yield from autre_gen()}\par
\par
\par
\par
